Arthur F. Powell
						PresidentChief Executive Officer

						afpowell@powellcapital.com

Mr. Powell brings
						over forty years of financing experience to his
						client base, specializing in public finance. 

Mr. Powell founded Powell Capital
						Markets in August, 1990. The firm�s business strategy
						encompasses the provision of investment banking,
						financial advisory services and lease financing services
						to governmental entities including states, cities,
						school districts, counties, local authorities,
						commissions, hospitals, prisons, and educational
						institutions. The high proportion of clients which that
						have remained with PCM through multiple transactions
						testifies to their appreciation of the expertise and
						innovative thinking that Mr. Powell brings to their
						financing challenges .
Prior to Powell Capital Markets,
						Mr. Powell was a principal in the investment banking
						firm of Grigsby Brandford Powell, Inc. where he was
						responsible for the firm�s marketing efforts in the
						eastern half of the United States. Previously, Mr.
						Powell served as President and founder of AGH Financial
						Corporation, a financial services institution
						specializing in equipment lease financings for municipal
						and corporate clients in the northeast. 
Mr. Powell is a 
						former member of the Newark Museum Board of Trustees, 
						the New Jersey Institute of Technology Board of 
						Trustees, St. James Preparatory School Trustee Board, 
						South Carolina State University Board of Visitors, The 
						Hospital Center at Orange Board of Trustees, NIDA, a 
						community development corporation sponsored by St. 
						Matthew A.M.E. Church, NJ Development Authority for 
						Small, Women and Minority Businesses, the Autism 
						Education Foundation of the Morris-Union Jointure 
						Commission and Seton Hall Leadership Institute.
Mr. Powell holds a Bachelor of
						Science degree in Mathematics from Purdue University. He
						maintains Series 52 and Series 53 licenses.

















