Julie K. Ehlers
						Senior Vice President

						jkehlers@powellcapital.com

Ms. Ehlers is a
						Senior Vice President at Powell Capital Markets. Her
						background includes extensive experience in public
						finance and quantitative techniques. Ms. Ehlers entered
						the field in 1989 in the Public Finance Department at
						Merrill Lynch, where she specialized in municipal
						reinvestments. After obtaining her MBA from Columbia
						University, Ms. Ehlers worked at Credit Suisse Financial
						Products where she analyzed interest rate swaps,
						mortgage-related derivatives and structured notes for
						municipalities and banks. 

In 1996, Ms. Ehlers transferred
						into the hedge fund group at CS First Boston, where she
						served as Quantitative Strategist until 1998. In this
						capacity she was responsible for integrating economic,
						technical and quantitative information into investment
						strategies, using products spanning interest rate swaps,
						swap options, foreign exchange forwards and foreign
						exchange options.
Ms. Ehlers provides expert
						structuring analysis and takes a primary role in
						transaction management and document review. She has
						structured taxable and tax-exempt transactions,
						refundings, restructurings and new money issues for a
						wide variety of issuers.
Ms. Ehlers has over 15 years�
						experience in various quantitative capacities in the
						fixed income field, has trained others in spreadsheet
						programming and fixed income pricing, and has completed
						both Munex-specific seminars: Introduction to Techniques
						for Quantitative Public Finance and Advanced Topics in
						Quantitative Public Finance.
Ms. Ehlers graduated Magna Cum
						Laude from Princeton University with an A.B. in History
						and received an MBA in Finance and Management from
						Columbia University. She maintains a Series 7 license.


















